snippet: Manufacturers have been weighed down by weak overseas growth and a strong dollar.
abstract: Commerce Department reports orders to American factories fell 0.2 percent in January, down from 3.5 percent in December; Labor Department reports new unemployment insurance applications rose 7,000 in latest week to seasonally adjusted 320,000.
lead_paragraph: Manufacturers have been weighed down by weak overseas growth and a strong dollar.

headline.main: U.S. Factory Orders Edged Down in January, but Data Also Supports Optimism
headline.print_headline: U.S. Factory Orders Edged Down in January, but Data Also Supports Optimism
